			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My take on this spell is this, I haven't battle tested it, per say; I have helped newbies with the 2-5 spiderlings/fire beetles trains =0); but I have found this out...target the tank, cast mesmerization on HIM, NOT the mobs...the spell will start with the tank in the center and branch out from there to encompass pretty much all the mobs attacking. Anyone who's researched this spell will know what I mean when I say:<BR>
<BR>
I just love seeing &quot;You have mesmerized a (insert mob)&quot; being spammed across my dialog box!<BR>
<BR>
The newbies really turn and drop their jaws with this spell, most of them think I chain casted on the beetle/spiderlings! <BR>
<BR>
One word to the wise, this spell is research ONLY (and I know 99% of enchanters have figured this out, the other 1% haven't found their guildmasters in the game yet!), unlike levitate and disempower...purchasable in shamen guilds; I used the concordance of research to bring my research from awful to feeble and said what the hey! I lucked out and got this spell, and disempower (again, bought mine in the Troll shamen guild in Grobb!) Anyways, be careful the pages aren't as plentiful as I thought they'd be and if your research is crappy, and it will be right out of 16, the calculated risk can give you high blood pressure or a stroke with each failure! =0P<BR>
<BR>
Kelilye, 16th seasoned dark elf enchantress
				</font>
