	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				On the last post:<BR>
<BR>
I am so glad I'm not the only enchanter in Norrath that has to contend with that problem.  Sheesh, it's just terrible.  Makes me not even want to bother with mezzing.  I finally get one mezzed, and a party member comes up out of nowhere to screw things up. <BR>
<BR>
Your hotkey idea is excellent.  I'm still low-level with my enchanter, which means all my groupmates are low-level also.  Which means they miss more often with their weapons.  Which means, on more than one occasion, I'll get something mezzed, and some mentally challenged group member will rush up and start swinging.  However, the mez doesn't break until he connects, and I'll be typing &quot;You idiot, stop attacking, help the rest of the group!!!!&quot;  Then he'll break the mez before I can finish.<BR>
<BR>
In short, playing an enchanter not only requires that you have brains, you have to make sure your groups also have brains, and slowly and carefully explain what your spells do.  <BR>
<BR>
Might be a good idea to hotkey the explanations too, it'll save time in the long run.  I think you'll be fine if you hotkey, &quot;OK, everyone use /assist on the puller, and ignore the other ones.  I'll mezz them, which will keep them stunned until they get attacked.&quot;  <BR>
<BR>
That alone is a decent explanation, and you may have to use it several times on the same group, hehe. <BR>
<BR>
You'd think those big dumb tanks would realize, &quot;Hmm, this thing is just standing here, and not attacking me or anyone else? How odd.  Perhaps I should go attack the thing that's killing my pal over there.  No, I want to attack the thing that won't fight back!&quot;<BR>
<BR>
In yellow &quot;Your mesmerization spell has ended&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Hehe, they ought to just group with wizards and forget about it.  Now I don't even bother with mezz, at least in dumb groups.  I just charm, and watch them all try to attack my pet.<BR>
<BR>
Another quick anecdote:  Once I had a charmed pet, and I had just begun telling my group, &quot;Don't help the pet on the next enemy, let him get beat up so we can kill him easier.&quot; Then the charm broke, and unfortunately, all I had managed to type was &quot;Don't help&quot;.  Hehe, I was OOM, and meleeing away, waiting for my group to jump in.  And waiting, and waiting!  When I finally said something, as I got down to 1 bubble of health one of them asked me, &quot;You said, &quot;Don't help!&quot;  I hadn't even realized that was the last thing I'd typed.<BR>
<BR>
In closing, I get into a lot of dumb groups, and I'm probably the dumbest, for playing an enchanter when I should be an ogre warrior!<BR>
<BR>
Hehe, if any of my former group mates read this, I wasn't talking about you, specifically.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Sweete
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
